

=Bio=

"I am a PhD student at the University of Lausanne in Switzerland. 
My research interests generally range around the relationship between consumption and well-being. While I currently focus on the psychological well-being of consumers, I generally assume a triple bottom-line approach towards well-being that involves the consumer, the environment and society at large. 

My PhD project focuses on various forms of peer-to-peer consumption and their potential contribution to the psychological well-being of consumers."


